The paper discusses a population-based optimization method, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.NE, cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on preserving diversity in the population, which is a key concern in optimization algorithms and can be addressed through various techniques such as fitness sharing and crowding (cs.LG). The paper also presents experimental results on optimization problems, which suggests a focus on empirical evaluation and experimentation (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the modification of a deletion operation, which is a software engineering concern and could potentially fall under the software engineering subcategory (cs.SE).
